        <abstract>
            <p>Discusses the power of land covered with snow to radiate heat.</p> 
<p>Criticises CL’s discussion of slavery [in <hi rend="italic">Travels in North America</hi> (1845)]. A review of CL’s book is in <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Mentions John Lindley’s views on carbonic acid gas and extinction;</p> 
<p>refers to the discussion of multiple and single creations in Humboldt’s <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi>.</p> 
            <p>The origin of volcanic craters of elevation.</p> 
<p>There is a popular demand for a new edition of <hi rend="italic">Principles</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Praises palaeobotanical work of C. J. F. Bunbury.</p>
        </abstract>
